Powered by RubiQube Ad Network The Police Command in Lagos State has arrested a fish farmer, Jeremiah Obifor, 61, for allegedly cutting off the hand of an 11-year-old boy, Goodluck Amechi for allegedly stealing fishes from his pond. The Spokesperson of the police in Lagos state, DSP Bala Elkana, said in a statement in Lagos on Sunday that the man cut off the boy’s hand who he suspected had come to steal his fish. Elkana said that the suspect was arrested after the victim’s foster mother, Doris Isaac, reported the matter at the Okoko, Police Station. He said that on June 7, at about 12:20pm the boy’s foster mother who resided at No.6 Ajanaku Street, Okoko, reported the matter at the Okoko police station. According to the police’s spokesperson Obifor attacked the 11-year-old boy with a machete and cut off his right hand and was rushed to Igando General Hospital for treatment. “The suspect alleged that he saw the victim around his fish pond and thought that he came to steal his fish and that was why he attacked him. “Investigation is ongoing and the suspect will be charged to court.” Elkana said.